# SYSTEM_SUMMARY.md — always keep in sync

On **every substantive task** (features, fixes, refactors that change behavior, routes, services, or important wiring):

1. **Append a row** to **`docs/SYSTEM_SUMMARY.md` §10 (Recent updates / changelog)** with date (UTC), a short summary, and the commit message when you commit.
2. **Edit earlier sections** when the change affects architecture: e.g. §3 routes/services, §2 dashboards, widget behavior — so §10 is not the only place that drifts.
3. **Trivial-only changes** (typos, formatting, one-line comments with no behavior change) do not require a changelog line unless the user asks.

This file is the project’s **single high-level reference**; treat an incomplete §10 as unfinished work before you finish the task.
